  "text": "Enterocytes possess ornithine decarboxylase, ornithine carbamoyltransferase and ornithine aminotransferase [CITATION_1] (Vaubourdolle et al. 1989) . It has been suggested that ornithine metabolism in enterocytes, by acting as a precursor for polyamine synthesis, may support gut morphology [CITATION_2] .",
